Attention! TUSD requires a new meal application at the start of each school year. Please apply online here:
https://mealapps.tusd.net/fma/ or click on the picture below.

With Distance Learning we will still be providing both lunch and breakfast for the next day, distributed curbside. Students will be charged according to their eligibility. Fill out your application today!

Lunch pickup times will be from 11:30 - 12:30.

Please be sure to apply for free or reduced meals, otherwise you will be charged full price.

You may drive-thru or walk up. Students must be present with their ID number to scan. Meals include lunch and breakfast

TRACY HIGH SCHOOL'S ACADEMY INFORMATION NIGHT FOR INCOMING 9TH GRADERS

WHEN: Thursday, November 7, 2019 at 6:00 PM
WHERE: Tracy High School Cafeteria
WHY: Meet the Coordinators of the Performing Arts Magnet, Agricultural/Scientific Academy and the International Baccalaureate Academy to find out if our programs are right for you!
WHO: Open to All interested students and their guardians who live in and around the Tracy Area.

Not only will you find out the benefits of our academies, information about applications, due dates, transfers and requirements will be discussed. There are a limited number of Intra-District Transfers available for our Academies.

Interested students are encouraged to come and join in the discussion! This is YOUR future!

For more information, please visit the THS Programs Page:
https://tracyhigh.tracy.k12.ca.us/academics-programs

post_text:
Local kids among high scorers at math tournament

Seven kids from Tracy and Mountain House led the field at the ninth annual San Joaquin County Math Tournament for fourth through sixth grades.

Out of 210 competitors, 11 were recognized as the highest scoring individuals. Two of them, Wenlun Liao and Samuel Chen, were members of a combined team from Monte Vista Middle School and South/West Park Elementary School. Amogh Janganure, Jishnu Nayak and Nikhil Gutlapalli all attend Hansen School. Andrew Mai is from Bethany School and Shanmukh Meka is from Questa School. The other four high scorers go to schools in Lincoln and Lodi school districts.

The team competition on March 30 included 36 teams and was won by Team 4 from Brookside School. Team 12 from Monte Vista-South/West Park and Team 8 from Hansen School tied for second place. Team 1 from Altamont School placed third, Team 3 from Bethany School came in fourth, and Team 35 from Questa School tied for fifth place with Team 7 from Elkhorn School.

Parents and community members are invited to examine instructional materials being considered for curriculum adoption by the Tracy Unified School District for middle school social and emotional learning.
The materials are on display from January 29, 2019 to February 28, 2019 in the Instructional Media Center of the District Services Center, 1975 W. Lowell Ave., from 8:30 a.m. to 4 p.m., Monday through Friday.
Public input is a vital part of Tracy Unified School District’s instructional materials adoption process and your comments will be considered by the TUSD Board of Trustees when making a decision about adopting these materials.
Any questions should be directed to Dr. Debra Schneider, Director of Instructional Media Services and Curriculum, at 830-3252.

post_text:
CLASSIFIED SUMMER ASSISTANCE PROGRAM

The Tracy Unified School District has elected to participate in the California Summer Assistance Program for classified employees in the 2019/2020 school year. Through Assembly Bill 1808, the State has set aside $50,000,000 in order to provide participating classified employees with up to one dollar ($1) for each one dollar ($1) that the classified employee elects to have withheld from his or her monthly paychecks (up to 10% of his/her salary). Please note that depending on the number of participating classified employees in this program, neither the District nor the employee may receive the full dollar for dollar match. More information regarding eligibility and enrollment information will be shared with employees once enrollment forms are received from the CDE.

TUSD Board Member Resigning; Board Accepting
Applications for Vacancy

(TRACY, CA) - TUSD Board Member Dan Arriola has resigned from the TUSD Board of Education effective November 30, 2018.

It is the intention of the Board of Education to appoint a person to fill the vacancy until the next trustee election in November, 2020.

Constituents residing in the TUSD elementary and/or high school boundaries who are interested in becoming a member of the Board of Education and contributing to the decision making process in the District are invited to submit an application (available at the District Office or online at https://www.tracy.k12.ca.us) along with a resume, to the Board of Education, Tracy Unified School District, 1875 W. Lowell Avenue, Tracy, CA 95376. The applications are to be received in the Superintendent’s Office no later than 5:00 p.m. on January 7, 2019.

Applicants will be interviewed at a special board meeting on January 17, 2019 @ 6:00 p.m.

post_text:
TUSD Families:

We have been monitoring the air quality by the hour and communicating as needed to the school sites. We have thoughtfully considered whether or not we should be closing schools at this time. Believing that the Tracy community consists of a high percentage of parents who commute to work, we have determined that it is best to keep schools in session at this time. It is in the best interest of our students to be supervised at school rather than left alone at home because parents are unable to find daycare on short notice. None of these decisions are easy but we are trying to make the best decision for our students. We are collaborating with our neighboring districts, Banta, Jefferson, and Lammersville, and we are all in agreement with this decision. If you still feel that your student would be better served by staying at home, that is a decision that you can make as a parent.

We will continue to keep you updated on any changes. Thank you.

We are hiring Substitute Food Service Workers
https://www.edjoin.org/Home/JobPosting/982967

Are you looking to do something different and exciting with a flexible work schedule and work when you want?
You decide when you work with a flexible opportunity that offers competitive pay and a chance to feel good about what you are doing serving nutritious meals to kids!

Tracy Unified School District has immediate and ongoing openings for dependable, personable, customer focused candidates to join our team as part time substitute food service workers.

Job Functions:
• Provide food service assistance and direct services to students
• Ability to work as part of a team as well as independently
• Monday through Friday, no nights or weekends
• Prior food service experience a plus
• Potential for permanent employment if desired

2 letters of reference required.
If you hold any food service certifications, please submit with your application.
Resume and Cover Letter optional
